cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.WEB, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the combination of web page information and social network data to create a personalized and socially connected web. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the analysis of how social media tunnels the flow of information, which falls under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the paper proposes techniques to rank information contained in web pages, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the structure and organization of the web, which falls under cs.WEB (World Wide Web). Finally, the paper discusses the delivery and organization of information specifically for each individual user, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
